    "Next, we (Section 3) briefly point out that, putting it mildly, perception has not exactly been treated in a deep way in the history of logicist AIdespite the fact that immediately instructive parables such as the Alice-Bob sketched above have been obvious since McKeon (1941) presented to humanity, in his Organon, the first formal logic, with algorithms for determining whether arguments expressed therein are formally valid.",
    "What follows is a section devoted to giving an historical perspective on our research (Section 4) and coverage of a considerable amount of related prior study.",
    "The next section lists the specific desiderata for argument-centric automated defeasible (= non-monotonic) reasoning that we seek and abide by and which are satisfied by the logico-mathematics, systems, and casestudy demonstration we present herein.",
